race.comment: Competitive. SWANSEE (4) brought strong Ascot form to resumption here over 1100m and needed it. Went back to Ascot following and found more like his best beaten 3L over 1400 when he led them up. Presents fitter again with more to give and will go close. FRIAR'S LEGACY (3) has been knocking on the door in town since his all-the-way Maiden win at Belmont. Raced a short-priced favourite narrowly beaten at Ascot last time over 1200m and Chris Parnham will give him every chance from an inside gate. TRUE FICTION (7) was beaten 1.2L in the same contest but ran a stronger number in an Open 3 at Belmont prior over this distance. At peak fitness now and has to be considered. PERFECT SISTER (5) comes back to provincial level third-up and is ready to show more like his best. That came at Group 2 level. In the mix.
